rComments: He is a great Professor, really wants you to do well and you should really ask him about things that might be of interest to you (especially for the term paper). Extremely accommodating and highly respected personality but doesnt act like it!! Loved the class
Beware!!! 20 multiple choice and 15 short answer question midterm GIVEN TO WRITE IN ONE HOUR!

He's an amazing professor. He grabs your attention in his lectures and his teaching style is amazing! I definitely recommend taking him. His tests are a little difficult but if you do the readings - both textbook and online readings, you'll be fine. Go to office hours and get to know him personally. He's a gem!

rComments: First of all, he is very attractive. Secondly, great professor he is really passionate about what he teaches. He tries hard to grab the attention of the class. His multiple choice only midterm was very straight forward and simple. The exam was even easier. Articles are necessary to pass. However, marked papers a tad hard. Overall, he's amazing.

Recommend coming to lectures, even if the slides are sometimes available online anyways, it was always an enjoyable lecture. Most of the material is common sense, but reading the chapters helps to prepare for the exams. The AI Kevin Meskill was also extremely helpful.

I took intro to criminal justice form him at IU and loved it. He's really into the material and makes it interesting to learn about. I would definitely take another class from him. Not one of the hardest classes I've taken but you do have to study for the tests.

Although the material was dull and a 3 hour lecture, he was engaging, went through the very clear slides quickly (thank god), and brought in a number of interesting guest speakers. He also replied to his emails quickly, which was helpful.
